Just 24 hours after this picture was taken by tourists, the same group stumbled across a very different scene. The very same calf was now standing over her mother's body, deep in grief over her death caused by poachers: killed by a poison tipped spear that had punctured her cheek. It was a ringside seat into the killings of elephants that are happening Africa-wide.

